s, like Ford's contempt trial decision, Staging the Trials of Modernism uncovers the conversations between the interior style of British Modern authors and the ways in which law began rethinking concepts like intent and the subconscious. Barleben’s fresh insights offer a nuanced look into the ways in which law influences literary production.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aCulture in literature. 0aEnglish literaturey20th centuryxHistory. 0aLaw in literature. 0aTrials in literature. 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aLAW / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2017z9783110547771oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066594940uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751242240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487512422423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487512422.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066594-9  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGCb2017  aZDB-23-DGGb2017